RAPPER Tabure “JR” Bogopa is preparing himself for his big day on popular music competition Idols South Africa. The music producer and businessman took to Instagram to share that the days that would see stars coming out of Mzansi had arrived. In his post on Tuesday, 12 July, he reminded his fans about his latest gig as one of the judges on the popular show, alongside Somizi Mhlongo, Thembi Seete and Proverb. ALSO READ : Top actress on maintaining popularity! “The journey of superstardom starts this Sunday for thousands who entered in hopes of being the next South African Idol,” he wrote. He also shared that the show would air every Sunday on Mzansi Magic’s channel 161 at 5.30pm. His fans immediately got excited, with musician George Avakian commenting: “Get them brother. Love you champ.” A post shared by Jr Bogopa (@jrafrika) 